content: This function utilizes a geometric shape, if present on ingestion, as a query parameter against a known geo political boundary service.  The result of this query should provided an ordered list of country codes, states, etc that the geometric shape overlaps.  This information enables data discoverability by country and state as a textual search vs a geospatial (mathematical) one.

content: Transformation of geometric coordinates to a known global standard coordinate system and datum (WGS84/EGM96).  Coordinates captured through the extraction process for geometric shapes may be tied to any coordinate reference system (CRS).  This function transforms the shape to a common standard prior to record creation.  Doing this on ingestion mitigates the need to transform every geometry on the fly in support of geospatial operations performed during filtering.
